SA Express to Spend $674 Million Renewing Its Fleet, Business Day Reports

-- B y   A n a   M o n t e i r o
-- 
2011-07-27T04:59:36Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-27/sa-express-to-spend-674-million-renewing-its-fleet-business-day-reports.html
SA Express, a South African state-
owned airline, will spend 4.5 billion rand this year renewing
its fleet, Business Day reported, citing Chief Executive Officer
Inati Ntshanga.  The company will establish a presence in  Ghana  over the
coming 12 months, using this as a hub for West Africa, the
Johannesburg-based newspaper reported.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Ana Monteiro at 
 amonteiro4@bloomberg.net  